The bullet-riddled body of a 34-year-old man who was kidnapped from his Scottburgh residence was found in the bushes in the Hlokozi area in Highflats. Three suspects were later arrested following a multi-disciplinary operation which comprised of various units within the SAPS as well as other law enforcement agencies. Captain Nqobile Gwala, provincial SAPS spokesperson said that police arrived at the crime scene and found the house full of blood and three vehicles were taken. She said: “Investigations led the team to Umzinto, Mpophomeni and Howick where the victim’s three vehicles were recovered. A total of three suspects aged between 21 and 34 were placed under arrest. The suspects led police to Hlokozi area in Highflats where the body of the victim aged 34 was found with gunshot wounds in the bushes. He sustained gunshot wounds to the upper body.” Charges of murder, robbery and kidnapping were opened at Scottburgh SAPS for further investigation. The suspects are scheduled to appear in the Scottburgh Magistrate’s Court soon.